body:
When I generated a waveform of the simulation of the following module, I noticed that in one moment the coverage counters of `if` and `else` branches are both incremented. The problem is with `if`/`else` in the first `always`.
```systemverilog
module t (/*AUTOARG*/
   // Inputs
   clk
   );

   input clk;

   integer cyc;
   initial cyc=1;

   logic      x;
   always begin
      if (cyc == 1) x = clk;
      else x = 0;
   end

   always @ (posedge clk) begin
      if (cyc != 0) begin
         cyc <= cyc + 1;
         if (cyc==10) begin
            $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
            $finish;
         end
      end
   end
endmodule
```
I ran verilator with options `--binary --coverage-line --trace-vcd --trace-coverage`.
A convenient way of reproducing this is replacing the file `test_regress/t/t_cover_line.v` with my example and running `test_regress/t/t_cover_line_trace.py --golden`. The output vcd file is `test_regress/t/t_cover_line_trace.out`.

I am attaching the part of the waveform that shows the problem.

